<TITLE> AL leader Abdul Jalil's health remains critical </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb. 28 (bdnews24.com) - The health of detained Awami League general secretary Abdul Jalil remains unchanged, hospital authorities said Thursday. Jalil's wife has appealed to prison authorities to allow him abroad for treatment. Deputy inspector general of prisons Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com: "I met Mr Jalil last (Wednesday) night." "I also talked with his wife by telephone." "We will be able to say more about Mr Jalil's condition after a medical board is formed Sunday," Siddiqui said. The AL leader is undergoing treatment at LabAid Hospital in the city. LabAid Group spokesperson Mesbah Azad told bdnews24.com Thursday that Jalil's condition remained unchanged. Jalil's assistant Md Akram Hossain said wife Rehana Jalil had appealed to the DIG of prisons, during their telephone conversation Wdnesday night, to allow her husband abroad for better treatment. Abdul Jalil was arrested on May 29 last year. He was admitted to LabAid Cardiac Hospital on July 15 after falling ill in jail. The AL general secretary is suffering from multiple ailments. Doctors say his kidneys are in critical condition, with his blood pressure rising uncontrollably. He also has heart and liver problems and his vision is impaired. bdnews24.
